Our Company
Wecker Associates is a world class consulting firm helping Fortune 500 companies with sophisticated data, statistical and mathematical analyses for corporate decision making, research and development, and expert testimony in litigations. We are looking for the right individual to join our team in Jackson, WY.

General Purpose
Data Analysts and Consultants work closely with Project Managers and Senior Consultants to solve client problems.

Desirable Qualifications
M.S. or B.S. in quantitative field;
Strong computer and data analysis skills (we use SAS, S-plus, Mathematica, and other scientific and general business software in a UNIX environment);
Good communication skills;
Ability to work collaboratively in an informal, collegial environment;
Ability to work effectively under deadlines.

Compensation and Benefits
Compensation strongly competitive with business, government, and academia;
Company-sponsored health and dental coverage.

Austin, TX
Pennybacker Capital is seeking a data analyst to join its Technology & Data Analytics team to lead data analytics and visualization efforts. The ideal candidate is excited about the opportunity to collaborate with a multidisciplinary team and has ample experience analyzing complex datasets and creating visualizations to support decision making. A sense of urgency, attention to detail and a passion for problem solving and creating impactful tools to drive change are key to success.
KEY RESPONSIBILITIES
Collaborate across teams to understand key metrics to measure performance and risk;
Manage data flow to Power BI dashboards and create new visuals and dashboards to support the real estate and infrastructure teams
Perform statistical analyses and identify trends and correlations with large datasets to inform and drive investment decisions, with an opportunity to grow into predictive modeling;
Ensure accuracy and integrity of data through unit tests, regression testing, and other means;
Work closely with investment and portfolio optimization teams to share insights and findings.

SKILLS AND EXPERIENCE
Proficiency with one or more scripting languages (Python, R, etc.) and capable of data wrangling and manipulation;
Experience with SQL and relational databases (SQL Server/Azure experience preferred);
Experience with Power BI, Tableau, or equivalent;
Accounting and/or finance experience preferred;
Experience with data ingestion via API and/or web scraping (e.g. Selenium, BeautifulSoup) preferred;
Bachelor’s degree in applicable field.
ASSESSMENT
To be considered for this position, please take the following steps:
1. Please email your resume to info@pennybackercap.com
2. In addition to your resume
The behavioral assessment should take less than 10 minutes to complete. It is not a test, and there are no right or wrong answers
